# Testing and Documentation Sync

## Verification

```bash
conda run -n remote-coder pytest -q
```

CI-style full pass:

```bash
PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD=1 conda run -n remote-coder pytest -q -p pytest_asyncio.plugin -p respx.fixtures
```

`PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD=1` prevents unrelated system pytest plugins from interfering.

Run focused tests first; broaden when shared behavior changes. Mock Telegram API, AI CLI, real Git repos, and external networks by default.

## Documentation Sync

- Release: follow `RELEASE.md`; update `CHANGELOG.md` and `CHANGELOG.ko.md`.
- New env vars, file settings, or Telegram commands: update README and related docs.
- Product scope changes: update `PLAN.md`.
- Rule or workflow changes: update `.cursor/rules/` and `AGENTS.md` together.

Use `EventLogger` with `LOG_RECORD_CONTEXT_KEYS` at Telegram, Job, Git, and Runner boundaries. Log message text as first-line preview only (max 80 chars).
